review_blob: Sweet caramel and fig smell. I noticed that many people said that this beer poured really clear, but I made sure to swirl the last fourth of the beer to stir up the sediment and boy did this beer pour beautifully cloudy. Amazing unfiltered amber. Thin head. Wonderful rich flavor and full palate. The best barley wine Ive tried yet.

This is one of my favorite beers! I love everything about it. Wonderful nose, beautiful appearance and I havent had a more refreshing hefeweizen that remained unfiltered. Great with the lemon as they suggest and is served in bars.
Very wonderful nose. Tart but clean tasting. Almost too much so, it seemed quite watery almost. Would try again though.

This is my favorite pumpkin beer out there so far. I love the really rich taste and the enticing aroma. If you like pumpkin beers this one is great, and one of, if not the only, pumpkin lager. The rest are usually ales.
raisin, vanilla, amber, hazy, frothy, heavy cloying sweetness, lightly bitter, average carbonation,

This beer was surprisingly sweet. It reminded me very much of Dogfishs Raison Detre. When I tried it beer for the first time I found myself savoring it so much that it went from ice cold out of the liquor store cooler to room temperature in my hand. Where that can be a killer with some beers this one took on a whole new interesting flavor, resembling the drinking of a really nice liquor neat. If one does not normally like the intense bitterness that IPAs offer, this is definitely worth a try. Not your common IPA by any means, but definitely now one of my favorites.
bread, citrus, herbs, dough, alcohol, amber, cloudy, aminimal head, medium sweetness, medium bitterness, medium sourness, soft carbonation, long finish, medium body,
